  "texts": [
    "So, on the path from small to large scale, we encountered a bottleneck in scale.Statistical physics is a bridge that connects microscopic and macroscopic aspects.",
    "It utilizes a probabilistic approach based on the understanding of the microstructure of matter and interactions between microscopic particles to provide a microscopic explanation for the physical properties and macroscopic laws of objects composed of a large number of particles.",
    "It is also known as statistical mechanics.",
    "Statistical physics is both a theory of physics and a methodology.",
    "The microscopic particles described in its framework can be molecules in gas, atoms in crystals, photons in laser beams and other conventional microscopic particles, as well as stars in the Milky Way galaxy, cars on highways, sheep in flocks, people in social groups, and so on."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}